content:
UPDATE: Upgrading to fish &gt;3 solves the issues now.
If you have decided to upgrade to the latest macOS Big Sur 10.14.6, you might have experienced an issue with slow autocomplete in fish-shell.
Due to change to read-only permissions for whatis 1 the man pages can&rsquo;t be updated for /usr/share/man. Therefore, the fish is switching to using apropos 2.
How to fix without updating? # # create backup cp /usr/local/share/fish/functions/__fish_describe_command.fish \ /usr/local/share/fish/functions/__fish_describe_command.fish.old # Taken from: https://github.com/fish-shell/fish-shell/issues/6270#issuecomment-548515306 echo &#34;function __fish_describe_command; end&#34; &gt; /usr/local/share/fish/functions/__fish_describe_command.fish Thank you fish community for such a quick solution 3.
